wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval: Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request parameter is invalid.
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-unsup:
Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request parameter specifies an unsupported version.

Parameters:
* $1 – the supported versions (comma-separated list)
* $2 – the number of supported versions
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval:
Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request parameter contains no valid field to specify the property ID to reconcile on.

Parameters:
* $1 – the version of the request parameter, e.g. 0.0.1
* $2 – the name of the field, e.g. urlReconcile

Error returned by the API if the “reconcile” request propertyId parameter is not of type URL.

Parameters:
* $1 – the name of the property, e.g. P123
* $2 – the name of the field, e.g. urlReconcile.
* $3 – the datatype of the provided reconcile property, e.g. string
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-unspe: Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter contains no version field in the entity input
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-inval:
Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter specifies an unsupported version.

Parameters:
* $1 is the specified (unsupported) version, $2 the supported versions, and $3 the number of supported versions
wikibasereconcileedit-editendpoint-quali: Error returned by the API if the “entity” request parameter specifies qualifiers and/or references. They are not yet supported.
